19/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The fourth round of talks between Pristina and Belgrade ended in Brussels on Wednesday (May 18th) with both delegations describing the two-day meeting as productive, regarding the freedom of movement, free trade, telecommunications and energy. 
No results, however, were presented and no agreement was struck. 
Kosovo representative Edita Tahiri said that missing persons and cultural heritage issues were also discussed. 
Her Serbian counterpart, Borislav Stefanovic, described the meeting as substantial.
In other news Wednesday, the Kosovo government decided to establish a ministry for diaspora. 
During a regular cabinet meeting, Prime Minister Hashim Thaci said the aim would be proper representation of Kosovo citizens living abroad. 
According to media reports, junior government coalition partner, the New Kosovo Alliance, will likely lead this new ministry. 
(Kosova Sot, Zeri, Express - 19/05/11; Klan Kosova, Kohavision, RTK, TV 21 - 18/05/11)
